This is a MISRA C compliant wrapper for LMDB written in C99.

## Rules

- camelCase for functions/variables/types, UPPER_SNAKE_CASE for macros/constants/enums
- Prefix public functions with `lmdbWrapper`, error codes with `LMDB_WRAPPER_ERR_`
- Type names use `_t` suffix (e.g., `lmdbWrapperErr_t`)
- 3-space indentation, no tabs
- Every closing `}` gets a comment (e.g., `} /* if result success */`)
- All code, comments, and documentation in English

## MISRA C (Mandatory)

- Validate ALL input parameters at function start
- NULL pointer → `LMDB_WRAPPER_ERR_NULL_PARAM`
- Invalid param → `LMDB_WRAPPER_ERR_INVALID_PARAM`
- Check ALL return values
- Single return point per function (use `result` variable + `if/else` chains)
- No `goto`, no implicit fall-through, no multiple returns
- All variables initialized at declaration
- Use `uint32_t`, `int32_t`, `size_t` (not `int`/`long`)

## Pattern

```c
lmdbWrapperErr_t lmdbWrapperFunc(const param_t *param)
{
   lmdbWrapperErr_t result = LMDB_WRAPPER_SUCCESS;

   if (param == NULL) {
      result = LMDB_WRAPPER_ERR_NULL_PARAM;
   } /* if null */

   if (result == LMDB_WRAPPER_SUCCESS) {
      /* do work, check return values */
   } /* if result success */

   return result;
} /* lmdbWrapperFunc */
```

## API

- `lmdbWrapperEnvCreate()` / `lmdbWrapperEnvClose()` — Environment lifecycle
- `lmdbWrapperPut()` / `lmdbWrapperGet()` / `lmdbWrapperDel()` — CRUD operations
- `lmdbWrapperStrerror()` — Error code to string

## Build

```bash
cmake -B build -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Debug && cmake --build build
cd build && ctest --output-on-failure
```
